</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Dusk" /><category term="Architecture" /><category term="Film" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Shooting film is a lot of extra work, expense, and time. But sometimes the warmth and richness makes it worthwhile, as in this evening photo of a Ryokan in Arashiyama, Kyoto. Kodak Ektar 100, processed in Negative Lab Pro/Lightroom.]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_DSC_0476-positive.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2025/2506_DSC_0476-positive.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Flowing Water・流水</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250602/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Flowing Water・流水" /><published>2025-06-02T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2025-06-02T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/flowing-water</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/250602/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
